        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2017-07-21 17:49:43.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThere is nothing hard-coded.  This is just adding an additional search mechanism for finding the kernel source -- in this case on a Red Hat system, at the lowest priority even.\n\nI can't see why trying harder to do just automatically do the right thing by default, instead of requiring the user to add more switches to his build command, is undesirable.",
